Step 1. Calculate the Gross Profit Margin.  
• Gross Profit Margin = (Gross Profit / Total Revenue) × 100%  
• Gross Profit = 300421.65, Total Revenue = 863371.65  
• Calculation: 300421.65 ÷ 863371.65 ≈ 0.3480, which is about 34.80%

Step 2. Calculate the Cash Flow to Debt Ratio.  
In the sample, the ratio was calculated as:  
  Cash Flow to Debt Ratio = (Net Cash Flow from Operating Activities) ÷ (Total Current Liabilities)  
For this problem:  
• Net Cash Flow from Operating Activities = –2419019.09  
• Total Current Liabilities is the sum of Accounts Payable and Taxes Payable = 5472810.00 + 43168.61 = 5515978.61  
• Calculation: –2419019.09 ÷ 5515978.61 ≈ –0.4386, which rounds to about –0.44
